# Mandatory project standards

## Essential reading — non-negotiable

Before writing or changing **any** Vala code, you **must** read the **entire**
**`docs/coding-standards.md`** file from start to finish. There is **no
alternative**. Partial compliance is a violation.

### How you must read it

- Use the **Read** tool on **`docs/coding-standards.md`** and read **every
  section**, from the first line to the last — including sections at the **end**
  of the file (e.g. method extraction, signal handlers, debug rules).
- Read it **before** you write, edit, or propose Vala code — not after, not
  in parallel with the first edit.

### What is forbidden

Do **not**:

- **Grep** or **search** the file instead of reading it.
- **Skim** — opening sections only, “the parts that seem relevant”, or jumping
  straight to a line number someone quoted.
- Rely on **summaries**, **memories**, **excerpts** quoted in chat, plans, or
  other rules — those are not substitutes for reading the source document.
- **Guess** conventions or assume you already know this project's rules.
- **Implement** until you have read the **whole** document in this session.

If you have not read **`docs/coding-standards.md`** in full during this task,
**stop** and read it before continuing.

You **must** follow **`docs/coding-standards.md`** on every Vala change. You
**must never** ignore it or treat it as optional guidance.

### After Vala edits (mandatory verification)

Before finishing the task, run the **Agent compliance gate** at the end of
**`docs/coding-standards.md`** (search changed `*.vala` for explicit local types,
no new helpers, etc.). See also **`.cursor/rules/vala-editing-gate.mdc`**.
Reporting "done" without running those checks is a standards violation.

### Other full documents (same rule — read all, do not grep or skim)

When the task requires it, read the **full** document the same way (Read tool,
start to finish):

- **`docs/build-rules.md`** — build or Meson changes
- **`docs/code-documentation.md`** — docblocks and API comments
- **`docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md`** — work from `docs/plans/*`
- **`docs/bug-fix-process.md`** — bug fixes (including propose → approval
  before applying code)

Canonical Vala style and patterns: **`docs/coding-standards.md`** (read it all).
Plans: **`docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md`** — Checklist for plans.
